de.gnwi.mfsim.model.util

Class FastListModel

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.swing.AbstractListModel<E>
      • javax.swing.DefaultListModel
        • de.gnwi.mfsim.model.util.FastListModel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, javax.swing.ListModel

    public class FastListModel
extends javax.swing.DefaultListModel
    Extended default list model for fast addElement-operations with deactivated fireContentsChanged event. See: http://bugs.sun.com/bugdatabase/view_bug.do?bug_id=4121430. This simple subclass of DefaultListModel allows one to disable list notifications, e.g. while making a big change to the model. The DefaultListModels fireXXX methods have been promoted from protected to public in this class so that clients can fire an appropriate ListDataEvent after the modifying the model with listeners disabled.
    Author:
    Achim Zielesny
